    </sec>
    <sec id="SEC2.3">
      <title>2.3 Min-Cut solution</title>
      <p>A <italic>cut</italic> on a weighted graph over vertices <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="btt238i25.jpg"/></inline-formula> is a partition of <italic>V</italic> in a nonempty set <italic>S</italic> and its complementary <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="btt238i26.jpg"/></inline-formula>. The <italic>cut-set</italic> of the cut is the set of edges whose end vertices belong to different sets of the partition. The <italic>minimum cut</italic> of the graph is the cut such that the sum of the weights of the edges belonging to its cut-set is minimum. If <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="btt238i27.jpg"/></inline-formula> is the adjacency matrix of the graph, finding the minimum cut is equivalent to finding <inline-formula><inline-graphic xlink:href="btt238i28.jpg"/></inline-formula> that minimizes the <italic>cut-function</italic>
